<%
  set_meta_tags(
    title: "Privacy Policy",
    description: "Privacy policy for jamesebentier.com — how we handle newsletter, analytics, and theme preference data under GDPR Art. 13.",
  )
%>

<div class="py-16 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <p class="font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-primary mb-2">Legal</p>
  <h1 class="font-mono text-3xl mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

  <div class="prose prose-base max-w-none text-base-content/80 space-y-6">
    <p>
      This notice explains what personal data jamesebentier.com collects, why, and what rights
      you have over it, per Art. 13 GDPR.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Controller</h2>
    <p>
      The party responsible for this site is identified in the
      <%= link_to "Impressum", impressum_path, class: "link link-primary" %>. For any data
      protection question, contact
      <a href="mailto:jebentier@gmail.com" class="link link-primary">jebentier@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Newsletter sign-up</h2>
    <p>
      When you subscribe to the newsletter I collect your <strong>email address</strong> and the
      following consent metadata:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
      <li>The date and time you gave consent (<em>consent_at</em>)</li>
      <li>Which page you signed up from (<em>consent_source</em>)</li>
      <li>A one-way SHA-256 hash of your IP address combined with a secret pepper
        (<em>ip_hash</em>) — the raw IP address is never stored</li>
      <li>A confirmation token and the time you confirmed (<em>confirmation_token</em>,
        <em>confirmed_at</em>), and the time you unsubscribe, if you do
        (<em>unsubscribed_at</em>)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Sign-up uses <strong>double opt-in</strong>: no email is sent until you confirm your
      address via the link in the confirmation email. All of this data is stored in our own
      Postgres database — there is no third-party email service provider. Every email includes
      an unsubscribe link.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Legal basis:</strong> your consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR).
      <strong>Retention:</strong> until you unsubscribe or request erasure.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Site analytics</h2>
    <p>
      This site records page views in our own Postgres database: the path visited, the
      referrer, optional campaign parameters (<em>utm_source</em>, <em>utm_medium</em>,
      <em>utm_campaign</em>), the time recorded (<em>recorded_at</em>), and whether the visit
      looks human or automated (<em>visitor_type</em>).
    </p>
    <p>
      This is <strong>cookieless</strong> and does not identify you individually: there are no
      cookies, no per-visitor IDs, no raw IP addresses stored, and no third-party analytics
      trackers. What's collected is minimal, aggregate traffic information.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Legal basis:</strong> legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR) in understanding
      aggregate site usage, weighed against the minimal, non-identifying nature of the data.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Theme preference</h2>
    <p>
      The site stores a single value — <code>theme</code> (your selected color theme) — in your browser's
      <code>localStorage</code>. This is strictly functional: it stays on your device, is never
      transmitted to the server, isn't shared with anyone, and isn't used for tracking.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Server logs</h2>
    <p>
      Like most web servers, this site generates standard Rails request logs, transiently, for
      operational and security purposes (e.g. diagnosing errors, detecting abuse). These are not
      used for analytics or profiling.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-mono text-xl mt-8 mb-4">Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under the GDPR you have the right to access, rectify, or erase your data, restrict or
      object to its processing, request data portability, and withdraw consent at any time
      (without affecting processing already carried out before the withdrawal). To exercise any
      of these rights, email
      <a href="mailto:jebentier@gmail.com" class="link link-primary">jebentier@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. The competent
      authority for this site is the
      <strong>Berliner Beauftragte für Datenschutz und Informationsfreiheit</strong>.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-base-content/50 mt-12">Last updated: 2026-07-22</p>
  </div>
</div>
